text: Charmes may refer to the following places in France: * Charmes, Aisne, a commune in the department of Aisne * Charmes, Allier, a commune in the department of Allier * Charmes, Côte-d'Or, a commune in the department of Côte-d'Or * Charmes, Haute-Marne, a commune in the department of Haute-Marne * Charmes, Vosges, a commune in the department of Vosges * Charmes-en-l'Angle, a commune in the department of Haute-Marne * Charmes-la-Côte, a commune in the department of Meurthe-et-Moselle * Charmes-la-Grande, a commune in the department of Haute-Marne * Charmes-Saint-Valbert, a commune in the department of Haute-Saône * Charmes-sur-l'Herbasse, a commune in the department of Drôme * Charmes-sur-Rhône, a commune in the department of Ardèche * Charmes- Chambertin, a grand cru vineyard in the department of Côte-d'Or == See also == * Charme (disambiguation)
